  "text": "A. Simulated system architecture For a 3 × 3 MGDM system, three channels are created in the fiber by the injection of light at three different offsets. A 3 × 3 transfer matrix H, describes the propagation channel in the fiber. Each transmitter launches a signal data in different group of modes. Each receiver detects the intensity generated by the GM in 3 differents circular areas. The output signal of each detector is a mixture of 3 signals [CITATION_1] . Simulation is performed using a 100m of MMF length. Two cases are studied. For the case 1, we use a (50/125µm) Graded Index (GI) MMF fiber with excitations conditions: w1=7µm, F1=0µm, λ1=850nm, θ1=0",
